HEADWORD: Shifty
<hw>Shift"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Full of, or ready
with, shifts; fertile in expedients or contrivance.</def>
<rj><au>Wright.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Shifty</qex> and thrifty as old Greek or modern Scot, there
were few things he could not invent, and perhaps nothing he could not
endure.</q> <rj><qau>C. Kingsley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

